    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1979-06-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1979-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="232"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d232">
                <head>232. Action Memorandum From the Assistant Secretary of State for Congressional
                    Relations (<persName corresp="#p_BDJ_1">Bennet</persName>) to Secretary of State
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d232fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Foreign Policy File,
                        P790089–0816. Limited Official Use. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_AJB_2"
                            >Atwood</persName> and cleared in <gloss target="#t_SPTA_1"
                            >S/PTA</gloss> by <persName corresp="#p_PDH_1">Popper</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1979-06-06">June 6, 1979</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">Phone Calls on Panama Implementing Legislation</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">ISSUE FOR DECISION</p>
                <p>Whether you will agree to call <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Henry
                        Kissinger</persName>, Dean Rusk and five congressmen to gather support for
                    the Panama Canal treaty implementing legislation.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">ESSENTIAL FACTORS</p>
                <p>The effort to reach a working majority on the implementing legislation in the
                    House reaches its climax this week and the White House has asked Cabinet
                    officers for support. You have been asked to call former Secretaries <persName
                        corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName> and Rusk to request their help with
                    certain Members. If you decide to call, you should ask <persName
                        corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName> to call John Rhodes, Bob Michel,
                    Bill Broomfield and John Buchanan.<note n="2" xml:id="d232fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> highlighted this sentence and
                        underlined “<persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName> to call John
                        Rhodes, Bob Michel, Bill Broomfield and John Buchanan.”</note> Rusk should
                    be asked to call Michel, Rhodes, Edgar Jenkins (D-Ga.) and Elliott Levitas
                        (D-Ga.)<note n="3" xml:id="d232fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> highlighted this sentence and
                        underlined “Michel, Rhodes, Edgar Jenkins (D-Ga.) and Elliott Levitas
                        (D-Ga.)”</note>
                </p>
                <p>We recommend that you phone the following congressmen urging them to vote against
                    amendments that would constitute treaty violations and using the general talking
                    points attached:</p>
                <p>Floyd Fithian (D-Ind.)</p>
                <p>Ben Gilman (R-N.Y.)<note n="4" xml:id="d232fn4">
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> placed a checkmark next to
                        this name.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Jim Leach (R-Iowa)</p>
                <p>Bob McClory (R-Ill.)<note n="5" xml:id="d232fn5">
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> placed a checkmark next to
                        this name.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Bob Young (D-Mo.)</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Recommendation:</p>
                <p>1. That you call <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName> and Rusk.<note
                        n="6" xml:id="d232fn6">
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> checked the approve option on
                        June 8.</note>
                </p>
                <p>2. That you call the Congressmen listed above.<note n="7" xml:id="d232fn7">
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> did not indicate his approval
                        or disapproval of the recommendation.</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0605" n="570" xml:id="pg_570"/>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Attachment:</p>
                <p>Tab 1—Talking Points<note n="8" xml:id="d232fn8">Attached but not printed.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
